"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The DateFormatter in matplotlib expects the date format to be in the format that datestr2num returns, which is the number of days since 0001-01-01 00:00:00 UTC, plus one. However, DateFormatter is being set to format the date as '%d/%m/%Y', which is not the format that datestr2num returns. Instead, datestr2num expects the date format to be in the American format '%m/%d/%Y' for conversion to matplotlib format.\",\n  \"patch\": \"13c13\\n<ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter(\\\"%d/%m/%Y\\\"))\\n---\\n>ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter(\\\"%m/%d/%Y\\\"))\\n\"\n}"